    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-06T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-06T08:00:00-05:00" n="282"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d282">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/775</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MIN1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-06T14:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 6, 1917, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received December 7, 6.15 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1126. Referring to following reported interview which appeared in the Swedish
                    newspapers and is supposed to have taken place between <persName
                        corresp="#p_JBGWV1">General Judson</persName>, the American military attaché
                    (no doubt the newspapers in error gave the name of <persName>Jackson</persName>
                    instead of <persName corresp="#p_JBGWV1">Judson</persName>), <pb facs="0363"
                        n="289" xml:id="pg_289"/> and <persName corresp="#p_TLDB1"
                        >Trotsky</persName> and which was contained in my telegram No. 1106.<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d282fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_283">p. 283</ref>.</note> This
                    has been causing a great deal of comment in Sweden. In an informal conversation
                    with the Foreign Minister yesterday on other matters he asked me as to the
                    authenticity of this report regarding statement of <persName corresp="#p_JBGWV1"
                        >Judson</persName>’s. I quote below <hi rend="italic">Dagens Nyheter</hi>
                    report regarding interview. …</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MIN1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
